<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-670-909  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 670 909.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Dec 10 1990 v7 n48 p12(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Cahners-Ziff Publishing Associates LP 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CIS, Marval link VAX system monitor, tracking tool. (ComputerInformation Systems' Robomon and Marval Software Ltd.'s Pursuit)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Donohue, James F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Information Systems Inc. (Product enhancement)Marval Software Ltd. (Product enhancement).andO;Product:   RoboMon 4.0 (Computer network software) (Product enhancement)Pursuit (Network management software) (Product enhancement).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionNetwork Management SoftwareCooperative AgreementEnhancementsInterface.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CIS, Marval link VAX system monitor, tracking toolandM;Computer Information Software (CIS) and Marval Software, have developed aninterface between ther VAX/VMS system software tools.andM;The CIS product is Robomon, which monitors VAX systems and fixes problems orsends warnings messages.andP;  The Marval product, Pursuit, is aproblem-management system that logs, tracks and reports user or systemproblems.andM;Separately, CIS announced that Polaroid has signed a five-year worldwidelicense that gives that company the right to use Robomon.andM;The pact between CIS and Marval gives Robomon a computer database in which tostore its warning messages.andM;&quot;Pursuit also supplies essential management information such as averageproblem turnaround time, complete category breakdowns and frequentlyoccurring problems,&quot; said David McGilvray, Marval's marketing manager.andM;&quot;When Robomon spots a problem on the system, it has two options.andP;  It can fixit or call upon human assistance,&quot; said Paul Roxan, CIS' marketing director.andM;&quot;If the problem has to be reported to the systems or operations staff, theymust then keep track of it to prevent it from being forgotten and to ensurethat it is solved,&quot; Roxan said.andM;&quot;By sending the problem directly into Pursuit's database, Robomon ensuresthat it will be correctly handled,&quot; he said.andM;The interface is part of Robomon release 4.0, according to Ken Leoni, CIS'U.S.andP;  product manager.andP;  Robomon prices range from $750 for a VAXstationproduct to $20,000 for a VAX 9000 product.andM;Users of earlier versions of Robomon can get the upgrade at no cost,according to Leoni.andM;Computer Information Systems can be contacted at 120 Wells Ave., Newton, MA02159, (617) 527-1550.andM;Marval Software Ltd. can be contracted at Claverton House, Longwood Court,Cirencester GL7 1YG, England, (011 44) 02850885201.andO;</TEXT></DOC>